    <p>The purpose of this activity is for students to apply their understanding of the area of rectangles to design a floor plan for a room. Students use their experience from the previous activity and consider what space is usable as they arrange the furniture. When students think about the dimensions of the different objects, the constraints of the space available, and the way things in a bedroom are usually arranged, they model with mathematics (MP4).</p>
